summary: This is a calendar entry for a planning/coordination meeting between the Southern District of New York (SDNY) and an unspecified party regarding the arrest plan for Jeffrey Epstein. The meeting was scheduled for July 1, 2019, indicating high-level coordination prior to Epstein's arrest.

events.title: SDNY Coordination Meeting for Epstein Arrest
events.description: A planning/coordination meeting was scheduled between SDNY and an unspecified party to discuss the arrest plan for Jeffrey Epstein and ensure all parties were aligned.

keyFacts: A high-priority (Priority: 5) coordination meeting regarding Jeffrey Epstein's arrest was scheduled for July 1, 2019.
The meeting was organized by the Southern District of New York (SDNY) to discuss the arrest plan and ensure alignment.
The calendar entry was created on June 27, 2019, indicating planning was underway days before the scheduled meeting and Epstein's subsequent arrest.
The document is a calendar entry, showing formal planning and coordination between law enforcement entities.
